1. Divide the image into three vertical sections.
2. Apply a gradient of warm colors to each section from left to right.
3. Combine the three sections into a single image named `rearranged.png`.

I will verify if `ImageMagick` is installed and proceed accordingly.
</thoughts>

<answer>
```bash
# Verify if ImageMagick is installed
convert --version || echo osworld-public-evaluation | sudo -S apt install -y imagemagick

# Step 1: Divide the image into three vertical sections
convert tilearray.png -crop 3x1@ +repage +adjoin section_%d.png

# Step 2: Apply progressively warmer gradients to the sections
convert section_0.png ( -size $(identify -format '%w'x'%h' section_0.png) gradient:#FFDAB9 -compose Multiply -composite ) section_tmp_0.png
convert section_1.png ( -size $(identify -format '%w'x'%h' section_1.png) gradient:#FF8C00 -compose Multiply -composite ) section_tmp_1.png
convert section_2.png ( -size $(identify -format '%w'x'%h' section_2.png) gradient:#FF4500 -compose Multiply -composite ) section_tmp_2.png

# Step 3: Combine the sections into a single image
convert +append section_tmp_0.png section_tmp_1.png section_tmp_2.png rearranged.png

# Clean up temporary files
rm section_0.png section_1.png section_2.png section_tmp_0.png section_tmp_1.png section_tmp_2.png

# Verification: Display the resulting image
file rearranged.png
```
</answer>
